Defendant Shane Dave Lewis in court with attorney Stephen Andrew Sargent.  Defendant Shane Dave Lewis in custody.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea hearing proceeds.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms.  Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility. 

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court imposed the following sentence:

Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 3 years.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 2 years   with credit for 74 days time served.  Defendant shall serve 1 year on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.   The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program, and  for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of his determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant.   The Court STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation to the State Department of Corrections for a period of three (3) years.
 * Court ordered defendant to provide a DNA sample. 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION (and Extended Supervision, if revoked):
 - Serve one (1) year condition time at the House of Correction, with Huber if employed and release to the Day Reporting Center.  No good time.  Should defendant be removed from the Day Reporting Center, balance of time would be served without release.
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment and treatment;
 - Urine screens;
 - No contact with the victim, Quentin D.;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Pay stipulated restitution in the amount of $31.26 to the victim of 14CF4871, Quentin D.; plus the DNA surcharge, all costs and surcharges.  Should defendant get revoked and be sent to prison, Court ordered monies to be taken from the Department of Corrections of up to 25% of prison funds.  Balance to be paid while on Extended Supervision.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

Filed,
